 and Politics: Roosevelt Versus Recovery, 1933\u20131938|publisher=Praeger|isbn=9780275935245|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bevan|first=Aneurin|year=1952|title=In Place of Fear|location=New York|publisher=Simon and Schuster|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|editor1-last=Birch|editor1-first=Kean|editor2-last=MacLeavy|editor2-first=Julie|editor3-last=Springer|editor3-first=Simon|year=2016|title=The Handbook of Neoliberalism|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781138844001|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Blaazer|first=David|year=2002|origyear=1992|title=The Popular Front and the Progressive Tradition: Socialists, Liberals, and the Quest for Unity, 1884\u20131939|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521413831|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Blair|first=Tony|year=1995|title=Let Us Face the Future|series=Fabian phamplets|location=London|publisher=Fabian Society|isbn=9780716305712|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bookchin|first=Murray|year=1998|title=The Third Revolution: Popular Movements in the Revolutionary Era|volume=2|location=London|publisher=Cassell|isbn=9780304335930|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Britain|first=Ian|year=2005|origyear=1982|title=Fabianism and Culture: A Study in British Socialism and the Arts, c. 1884\u20131918|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521021296|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Brandal|first1=Nik|last2=Bratberg|first2=\u00d8ivind|last3=Thorsen|first3=Dag Einar|date=21 February 2013|title=The Nordic Model of Social Democracy|publisher=Springer|page=7|isbn=9781137013279|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Branch|first=Taylor|year=1989|title=Parting the Waters: America in the King Years, 1954\u20131963|location=New York|publisher=Touchstone|isbn=9780671687427|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bronner|first=Stephen Eric|year=1999|title=Ideas in Action: Political Tradition in the Twentieth Century|location=Oxford|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield Publishers|isbn=9780847693870|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Burns|first=James MacGregor|year=1956|title=Rooseve